				Amador County&amp;#39;s Shenandoah Valley is the heartland of robust, old-vine Zinfandel. Amador is renowned for producing California&amp;#39;s finest zinfandels, some of them crafted from 19th-century vines. In recent years, Amador vintners have also begun producing delicious Rh&amp;ocirc;ne and Italian varietal wines, including syrah, viognier, barbera, and sangiovese. Along with Amador&amp;#39;s prized zinfandels, these bottlings have earned enthusiastic praise from critics and wine lovers worldwide.
			
				
					
						
							
								
						
					
				
			
		
	



	
		
			
				
			
				
					
