The St. George Historic Hotel is located in Volcano-the &amp;ldquo;Gem of the Mother Lode&amp;rdquo;, slightly off the beaten path in the Sierra Nevada Foothills of California.&amp;nbsp;

&amp;nbsp;

While some guests may prefer to stay in the more modern rooms of the annex, the original architecture and ambiance of the main building will offer guests a feeling of serenity and simpler times. Depending on who you talk to, it is rumored that ghosts roam the second and third floor of the hotel, with one room specifically being haunted.&amp;nbsp; The lovely and magical grounds of the St. George are a joy in every season.

&amp;nbsp;

The main floor of the St. George Hotel has 3 sections: The &amp;ldquo;Parlor&amp;rdquo; with 12-foot ceilings and a grand fireplace; The &amp;ldquo;Dining Room&amp;rdquo; home to some of the finest food in the County; and The &amp;ldquo;Whiskey Flat Saloon&amp;rdquo; which was added to the main structure in the 1930&amp;rsquo;s and is a great place to have a drink, explore the bar memorabilia on the walls, and meet the locals.

